    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This function creates a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CGAffineTransform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " structure, which you can use (and reuse, if you want) to scale a coordinate system. The matrix takes the following form:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-1966736",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "1966736",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Because the third column is always "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0,0,1)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CGAffineTransform"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " data structure returned by this function contains values for only the first two columns. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "These are the resulting equations used to scale the coordinates of a point (x,y):"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-1966741",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "1966741",
                "title": "Figure 2"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you want only to scale an object to be drawn, it is not necessary to construct an affine transform to do so. The most direct way to scale your drawing is by calling the function "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1454659-cgcontextscalectm"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
